CatDescriptText: Cutline of related image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper January 11, 1941, pg. 10, reads: "Board of National Musicians Meet in Pittsburgh - Highlighting the holidays in Pittsburgh was the mid-winter board meeting of the National Association of Negro Musicians.  This charming picture was taken at the Foster Memorial Hall on the occasion of the Artists' Concert in honor of the board members.  They are, left to right: Blanche K. Thompson, of New York; Josephine Inness, of Chicago; Henry L. Grant, Washington, D. C., past president and organizer; Mary Cardwell Dawson, president, Pittsburgh; Clarence Hayden Wilson, vice-president, St. Louis; Florence B. Price, chairman of Symphony, Chicago."
TitMainTitle: National Association of Negro Musicians board members Blanche K. Thompson, Josephine Inness, Henry L. Grant, Mary Cardwell Dawson, Clarence Hayden Wilson, and Florence B. Price seated in Foster Memorial Hall, Oakland
